mixin docs_fontSize(classname)
  - classname = classname || {}
  p.
    These are two groups of atoms. The first group simply sets the font size of an element.
    The second group uses the #[code.docs-code .font-size-el()] mixin,
    for maintaining vertical rhythm.
  p.
    See all the font sizes in the source file #[code.docs-code /src/__settings.less],
    and all atoms in #[code.docs-code /src/_atom.less]
  pre.docs-pre.
    @g-font_size_peta: 96/16;
    @g-font_size_tera: 64/16;
    @g-font_size_giga: 48/16;
    @g-font_size_mega: 32/16;
    @g-font_size_kilo: 24/16;
    @g-font_size_norm: 16/16;
    @g-font_size_mill: 12/16;
    @g-font_size_micr:  8/16;
    .-fz-norm { font-size: @g-font_size_norm * 1em; }
    .-fz-el-norm { .font-size-el(@g-font_size_norm); }
  figure.docs-figure
    figcaption.-mb-1vru.
      Use #[code.docs-code .-fz-*] on inline elements.
      Numbers shown are font-sizes(ems).
    ul
      li #[u.-fz-peta universe] (6.00)
      li #[u.-fz-tera galaxy  ] (4.00)
      li #[u.-fz-giga star    ] (3.00)
      li #[u.-fz-mega planet  ] (2.00)
      li #[u.-fz-kilo asteroid] (1.50)
      li #[u.-fz-norm molecule] (1.00)
      li #[u.-fz-mill atom    ] (0.75)
      li #[u.-fz-micr quark   ] (0.50)
    pre.docs-pre.
      &lt;li&gt;&lt;u class="#[u -fz-peta]"&gt;universe&lt;/u&gt; (6.00)&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;&lt;u class="#[u -fz-tera]"&gt;galaxy  &lt;/u&gt; (4.00)&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;&lt;u class="#[u -fz-giga]"&gt;star    &lt;/u&gt; (3.00)&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;&lt;u class="#[u -fz-mega]"&gt;planet  &lt;/u&gt; (2.00)&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;&lt;u class="#[u -fz-kilo]"&gt;asteroid&lt;/u&gt; (1.50)&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;&lt;u class="#[u -fz-norm]"&gt;molecule&lt;/u&gt; (1.00)&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;&lt;u class="#[u -fz-mill]"&gt;atom    &lt;/u&gt; (0.75)&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;&lt;u class="#[u -fz-micr]"&gt;quark   &lt;/u&gt; (0.50)&lt;/li&gt;
  figure.docs-figure
    figcaption.
      Use #[code.docs-code .-fz-el-*] on block elements.
      Numbers shown are font-sizes(ems)/line-heights.
